00:44:57,777 --> 00:45:02,784
And just that process itself is undermining the delusions.

403
00:45:03,186 --> 00:45:04,789
It's undermining the delusions.

404
00:45:04,869 --> 00:45:09,974
It has this sort of back effect on the observer, on the feeler.

405
00:45:10,494 --> 00:45:13,577
So that way of looking at life is changing.

406
00:45:14,318 --> 00:45:22,327
So this change in the way we're looking at life, it's sort of like a clock, it's just moving over in little seconds.

407
00:45:23,409 --> 00:45:32,838
And when it's done a full turn, there's a sort of seeing which is deep enough to maintain a certain level, a certain attitude to life,

408
00:45:33,088 --> 00:45:37,663
Which means that the sort of suffering I had before that is not possible.

409
00:45:38,726 --> 00:45:40,210
I can't go there again.

410
00:45:40,231 --> 00:45:44,905
I mean, it happens just in ordinary things like, you know, you might get...

411
00:45:45,458 --> 00:45:54,032
I remember just in my own small experience of getting so drunk so often and such a pain in the head that I woke up on a gravestone, I remember.

412
00:45:54,474 --> 00:45:57,038
And I said to myself, what if I only get tipsy?

413
00:45:57,599 --> 00:46:09,340
And from that time on, apart from when somebody fooled me to drink too much wine, said there wasn't much alcohol in it, I never got drunk again.

414
00:46:10,079 --> 00:46:14,202
It was just recognizing that the pain of getting drunk wasn't worth it.

415
00:46:15,003 --> 00:46:16,945
And I thought to myself, what if I only get tipsy?

416
00:46:17,226 --> 00:46:18,668
And I only did get tipsy, and it was great.

417
00:46:18,869 --> 00:46:19,409
I was fine.

418
00:46:19,708 --> 00:46:20,389
I was happy with that.

419
00:46:21,190 --> 00:46:33,003
And so that's a really bad example of what happens when you lift yourself up to a level of understanding and clarity, and you just can't go there.

420
00:46:33,784 --> 00:46:38,550
So that's why it's said that somebody who's obtained the first path and fruit can't go to hell.

421
00:46:39,003 --> 00:46:40,405
It can't go into a hell realm.

422
00:46:40,826 --> 00:46:44,371
Now, if you want to think of it as a separate realm, fine.

423
00:46:44,391 --> 00:46:52,224
But what it's actually saying is you can't, by your actions, make yourself fall into those desperate states that you once did.

424
00:46:52,724 --> 00:46:53,465
That's what it's saying.

425
00:46:54,226 --> 00:46:57,452
You see?

426
00:46:57,472 --> 00:46:59,456
So that's how it works.

427
00:46:59,496 --> 00:47:04,163
If I were to sort of put all that together in a nutshell, my goodness.

428
00:47:04,704 --> 00:47:05,144
So...

429
00:47:07,588 --> 00:47:12,735
What we're looking at essentially is this fundamental misunderstanding.

430
00:47:12,876 --> 00:47:13,878
We call it a delusion.

431
00:47:13,998 --> 00:47:15,239
It's a misunderstanding.

432
00:47:16,442 --> 00:47:19,626
It's a misunderstanding about who we are and what we are.

433
00:47:23,532 --> 00:47:29,860
And that which has made this misunderstanding is not in itself stupid.

434
00:47:30,141 --> 00:47:32,244
It's not an ignorance that's come out of stupidity.

435
00:47:32,264 --> 00:47:34,126
It's an ignorance that's come out of not knowing.

436
00:47:35,610 --> 00:47:37,291
So the process of that not knowing

437
00:47:38,538 --> 00:48:02,925
it brings us into this suffering from the heart's point of view it's not coming from a position of evil some sort of disposition where it's going to create it no it's coming from a point of innocence it doesn't know what harm is it doesn't know that it is doing harm so we start from these two positions we start from an a simple not knowing and an innocence

438
00:48:03,208 --> 00:48:06,773
Then making this mistake, all we're trying to do is make ourselves happy.

439
00:48:07,253 --> 00:48:08,675
And in so doing, we create mayhem.

440
00:48:09,416 --> 00:48:10,396
We create all this suffering.

441
00:48:10,978 --> 00:48:13,280
And then we come across the Buddha's teachings.

442
00:48:13,300 --> 00:48:13,701
Yippee.

443
00:48:14,501 --> 00:48:18,586
And he points out that we're looking at things from three different angles, which are wrong.

444
00:48:18,887 --> 00:48:19,969
We think things are permanent.

445
00:48:20,009 --> 00:48:21,911
We think we can really get happiness.

446
00:48:22,592 --> 00:48:24,373
And I really am.

447
00:48:24,414 --> 00:48:26,275
And this is what I really am.

448
00:48:26,617 --> 00:48:27,356
And I can do it.

449
00:48:28,137 --> 00:48:30,380
And when we begin to undermine those...

450
00:48:31,153 --> 00:48:33,619
the relationship to life begins to change.

451
00:48:33,958 --> 00:48:35,822
Our relationship to life begins to change.

452
00:48:37,545 --> 00:48:45,019
And eventually we arrive at a state, hopefully by New Year, when there is no suffering left.

453
00:48:45,840 --> 00:48:50,068
And what we mean by that, let's not confuse this, it's not that the body doesn't give us pain.

454
00:48:50,108 --> 00:48:53,094
Remember the Buddha died from some sort of gastroenteritis.

455
00:48:53,782 --> 00:49:06,215
But there is no way that this essential nature within us, this Buddha within, this nirvanic element, can fall into a relationship where it causes suffering.

456
00:49:07,677 --> 00:49:08,538
Who's suffering?

457
00:49:10,278 --> 00:49:11,159
The Buddha suffers.

458
00:49:12,121 --> 00:49:15,605
The Buddha's suffering until it realises where the mistake is.

459
00:49:16,005 --> 00:49:17,085
And then it becomes Buddha.

460
00:49:19,208 --> 00:49:21,090
Which is a very strange thing to say.

461
00:49:22,436 --> 00:49:30,246
People don't see the Buddha as suffering because the word Buddha is, of course, referring to that ultimate state, the one within.

462
00:49:31,047 --> 00:49:33,911
But it's the suffering that we're experiencing.

463
00:49:33,931 --> 00:49:37,114
When we experience suffering, it's the Buddha within that suffering.

464
00:49:38,155 --> 00:49:39,478
Remember, the body doesn't suffer.

465
00:49:39,538 --> 00:49:42,601
It's just got physical discomfort.

466
00:49:42,641 --> 00:49:44,364
It doesn't know it's suffering.

467
00:49:44,963 --> 00:49:46,306
The heart doesn't know it's suffering.

468
00:49:47,166 --> 00:49:50,871
There is depression, but the heart isn't saying, oh, I'm suffering.

469
00:49:51,132 --> 00:49:52,072
It doesn't have consciousness.

470
00:49:53,487 --> 00:49:55,289
Thoughts don't have, they don't think themselves.

471
00:49:56,572 --> 00:49:58,135
They don't think about thinking themselves.

472
00:49:58,155 --> 00:50:03,784
There's always something behind all that which is clocking it, which is experiencing it.

473
00:50:04,746 --> 00:50:12,240
And that process of disengagement, you see, is the process of liberation.

474
00:50:12,260 --> 00:50:18,110
And that process of liberation always takes us, when we're fully, even in the short little moments,

475
00:50:18,394 --> 00:50:44,233
experiences of liberation that we have it always takes us back into the world you see takes us back into the world but in a growing way of interconnectedness and that's what we call love I can only hope that my words have been of some of some advantage

476
00:50:44,635 --> 00:50:47,266
I've not caused even greater confusion.

477
00:50:47,829 --> 00:50:54,139
And that by your determined effort, you will become fully liberated sooner rather than later.

